cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.CL

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and image processing techniques to improve optical character recognition (OCR) performance. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms and optimization techniques, which are commonly studied in sub-categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the impact of text image super-resolution on OCR accuracy, which falls under the scope of natural language processing (NLP) and could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
